    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-04T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="1266"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1266">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2512</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-04T17:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 5, 6 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3843. Your 2956, May 1, 4 p. m. Search of records here shows no correspondence
                    relative to hospital supplies in transit subsequent to Department’s reply dated
                    November 10 to my despatch 1673.<note n="1" xml:id="d1266fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_1053">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, Supplement, p.
                            1053</ref>.</note> Foreign Office states verbally no reply received to
                    note sent Spanish Ambassador on October 15 and nothing known of any statement
                    made by British Government last November.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
